<h2>Change of Name and/or Ownership</h2>
<p>Regulatory Guide 8.2 describes general conditions that would require issuance of a new certificate of registration due to a change in name and/or ownership of a registrant using medical, dental, veterinary, or industrial x-ray machines, lasers, accelerators, or minimal threat machines, and radiation services. It also describes conditions involving a change in name and/or ownership that may require an amendment to an existing certificate of registration rather than issuing a new certificate of registration. Any change in name and/or ownership will be evaluated on a case-by-case basis by the Department of State Health Services, Radiation Safety Licensing Branch.</p>
<p><a title="Regulatory Guide 8.2 - Guidelines for Issuing Certificates of Registration Due to a Change in Name and/or Ownership" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=20044">Regulatory Guide 8.2 - Guidelines for Issuing Certificates of Registration Due to a Change in Name or Ownership</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 42KB)</span></p>
<p>Title 25 Texas Administrative Code (TAC), chapter 289 prohibits the transfer of certificates of registration to other persons unless the Agency provides its consent in writing. The Agency should be notified in writing within 30 days of a change in name and/or ownership of an existing certificate of registration.</p>

